# Web search

- Prefer **official documentation** (Tauri, React, SQLite, MDN, etc.) over tutorials and blog posts.
- Prefer **latest stable APIs** and current docs; do not assume old versions.
- **Do not append years** (e.g. 2024, 2025) to search queries unless you need version- or time-specific results.
- Prefer **specs and source docs** over third-party tutorials. Prefer GitHub repos and official sites.
- Avoid low-signal SEO: listicles, “X ways to…”, Medium, dev.to unless they are the only useful source for a narrow topic.

When a version is relevant, choose the **latest stable**; avoid outdated tutorial-driven code.
